**Reading the summary statistics:**

- `lead_time` ranges from 0 (same-day booking) to 629 days ahead, with a median around 45 days. This wide range means lead_time will dominate any distance-based algorithm if left unscaled.
- `adr` (our regression target) has a median of about 95 euros/night. The standard deviation (~47) is large relative to the mean, suggesting a spread-out distribution that a single linear model may struggle with.
- `is_canceled` has a mean of 0.37, meaning **37% of bookings cancel**. This is moderately imbalanced: the majority class ("kept") is 63%. We will need `stratify` when splitting and `class_weight="balanced"` when fitting the classifier.

