## 5. Baseline First

Before training any learned model, establish what a **zero-effort strategy** achieves. A baseline is the simplest possible prediction that requires no learning:

- `DummyRegressor(strategy="mean")`: always predicts the mean ADR of the training set.
- `DummyClassifier(strategy="most_frequent")`: always predicts "not cancelled" (the majority class).

If your trained model cannot beat these baselines, it has not learned anything useful from the features. The baseline sets the **floor** that every subsequent model must clear.

::: {#65c640d7 .cell execution_count=14}
``` {.python .cell-code}
dummy_reg = DummyRegressor(strategy="mean")
dummy_reg.fit(X_train_s, y_train)
y_pred_dummy_reg = dummy_reg.predict(X_test_s)

dummy_mae  = mean_absolute_error(y_test, y_pred_dummy_reg)
dummy_rmse = root_mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred_dummy_reg)
dummy_r2   = r2_score(y_test, y_pred_dummy_reg)

logger.info("DummyRegressor (always predicts training mean ADR):")
logger.info(f"  Constant prediction: {dummy_reg.constant_[0]:.2f} euros/night")
logger.info(f"  MAE:  {dummy_mae:.2f} euros")
logger.info(f"  RMSE: {dummy_rmse:.2f} euros")
logger.info(f"  R2:   {dummy_r2:.4f}  (always 0.0 by definition for mean strategy)")
logger.info("This is the floor. Every model we train must beat MAE < {:.2f}.".format(dummy_mae))
```

