## Summary

| Concept | Key takeaway |
|---|---|
| **sklearn API contract** | `fit()` on training data only; `transform()` / `predict()` on any split |
| **Feature scaling** | StandardScaler zero-centres each feature; required before gradient-descent models |
| **Train/test split** | Fit the scaler on `X_train`, then transform `X_test` -- never the other way around |
| **Stratified split** | Use `stratify=y` for imbalanced classification targets |
| **Baseline first** | DummyRegressor and DummyClassifier set the minimum acceptable performance floor |
| **class_weight="balanced"** | Essential for LogisticRegression on imbalanced targets; prevents predicting the majority class every time |
| **Cross-validation** | 5-fold CV gives a mean and std over model performance, far more informative than a single split |
| **Learning curves** | Diagnose capacity limits (plateau) and overfitting (large train/val gap) |
| **joblib** | Save the full inference bundle (scaler + model + features) so prediction is self-contained |
:::

